# Audit trail and record tables (required)

These requirements are **not optional**. Every new page and record must ship with them.

## 1. Audit footer on every `AppShell` page

Every view wrapped in `AppShell` **must** pass the `audit` prop.

### List / admin / hub pages (no single record id)

```tsx
<AppShell title="…" audit={{ moduleLabel: "Enquiries" }}>
```

### Record detail / singleton config pages

```tsx
import { auditMetaFrom } from "@/lib/audit";

<AppShell
  audit={{
    entityType: "organization",
    entityId: record.id,
    meta: auditMetaFrom(stored ?? record),
  }}
>
```

**Checklist**

- [ ] `audit` prop on every `AppShell` — never omit
- [ ] Detail/singleton pages use `entityType` + `entityId` + `meta` (not only `moduleLabel`)
- [ ] New types in `web/src/lib/audit.ts` and field labels in `web/src/lib/audit-diff.ts`
- [ ] Saves call `persistRecordAudit()` outside React `setState` updaters

## 2. Line tables on every record

Repeating child data needs line table config, Supabase child table + migration, data-api/mappers, and a record tab UI.

## 3. Handoff verification

1. Footer visible on the page
2. Save logs one audit event with field detail in **Full audit trail**
3. Line tables persist after refresh

See also: `record-audit-footer.tsx`, `audit-mutation.ts`, `record-line-table.tsx`.
